RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 5, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FANCY PAYNTER stalked the early leader from the four path, maintained the position through the turn and into the upper stretch, was strongly urged at the three sixteenth pole, responded well and found more, closed down the outside passing rivals and gaining ground all the way to the wire getting up for the win in the last jump. TRAFFIC CONTROL vied for the lead an raced on the rail, set the pace, rated in hands, started to draw away from the pack at the the quarter pole, had a length lead by the eighth pole, was in command, was caught in the last jump by a hard charging outside rival and just missed. WINGS FOR ENO stalked the leader from the three path, raced in between foes, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, improved position, was encouraged and responded well by closing down the stretch getting up for third. RAUL'S ENCANTO vied for the lead, stalked the front runner by a head until the five sixteenth pole, flattened out in the stretch. HALF A BUCK stalked the pace, raced on the rail and maintained the same position through out. MAJOR CONTENDER was off mid pack, raced four wide, drew next to another rival and worked as a set down the stretch. MR FROST raced in the two path as he stalked the early leaders, raced in between rivals, shuffled back through the turn, hooked another rival in the stretch run. PREFERITO DA BARBI raced from off of the pace in the three path and gained mildly late. CLERIC raced off of the pace, stayed on the rail, saved ground through out but had no kick. SILKY'S DANCE raced from mid pack in the six path and made no impact. STREET ART raced from mid pack in the five path, shuffled back and faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main trac k at 1 Mile and 70 Yards).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AVENDORE was off in the middle of the field, raced on the rail, improved position, stalked going in the turn, shifted into the three path near the eighth pole and was under encouragement, willingly continued to drive past rivals, cleared the early leader by the last sixteenth marker and took the win. ZEEROCK raced from off of the pace, stayed on the rail, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, gained ground through the turn, was asked and responded by closing with each stride and out finishing the rest getting up for the place spot. CAPETOWN CANDY vied for the lead, raced on the rail and commanded the fractions, was under a drive down the stretch, was collared by the sixteenth pole but held on for third. JUST A WIN stalked the front runners from the four path, moved up while racing down the back side, raced in between foes, drew next to the front runners near the three eighths pole, entered into the upper stretch and had no kick. T J'S FIRST raced off of the pace in the two path, mild gain late. BELL PEPPER raced from mid pack in the three path, raced in between rivals, struggled to switch leads, in the stretch, still closed well but to no avail. LUCKY HARBORAGE raced from off of the pace, stayed on the rail, settled in hands, bid at the quarter pole, and under a drive closed well, not enough today. ELMO'S SECRET raced from the middle of the field, stayed in the four and five paths, maintained that position through out. HIGH DONNA was off and raced from mid pack, raced on the outside in the five path, launched a bid at the half mile marker, drew next to the front running horses at the the three eighths pole, then faded. SMUGLERS BLUES stalked the leader from the two path, inched closed and was just off the leader by a head, was joined by other rivals on the front end and began to loose ground. OCEAN FLEET stalked the pace from the two path and fell back before the quarter pole.
